description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Public Health Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Cheshire East 0-19 Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band: &lt;/strong&gt;5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 33 hours all year round &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base: &lt;/strong&gt;North Team Wilmslow Knutsford and Poynton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract: &lt;/strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Ref: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wirral Community NHS Foundation Trust has been commissioned by Cheshire East Local Authority as their chosen preferred provider for the Cheshire East 0-19 Service (Integrated Children’s Division).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help us to continue to transform our services, to enable the leadership and delivery of a robust healthy child programme and public health agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting Public Health Nurse opportunity has arisen in the North [Wilmslow Poynton and Knutsford) area. We are looking to recruit to a Term Time Only position. If you want to make a difference to the health of children within Cheshire East we would very much like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public Health nursing within the 0-19 team is a dynamic and exciting service to work in and becoming a Public Health Nurse with us will give you the opportunity to work within the health promotion and public health domains. As a Public Health Nurse you will support delivery group based health promotion interventions and individual work with children, young people and their families to address local needs. You will also support the immunisation team to deliver immunisations in primary and secondary school settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the ability to work autonomously as well as part of a skill mixed team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work closely with neighboring teams, which include education,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to provide services in response to identified need, whilst working in partnership with Cheshire East Local Authority to take the local children’s agenda forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have enhanced interpersonal skills to identify low protective factors and indicators of abuse or neglect, or anxiety and low confidence in young people. Using your skills, you will develop strength based plans of care to build resilience, promote positive wellbeing and achieve improved health outcomes for children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have good organisational ability and be able to communicate effectively with children, young people and their families, both in the home, school and other community/education provider settings. &lt;span&gt;An in depth&lt;/span&gt; A knowledge of the current health agenda relating to children’s services and both school nursing and health visiting is &lt;span&gt;essential&lt;/span&gt;. desirable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No two days are the same when working with children and young people, every day will have its challenges and successes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working with children and families is desirable but not essential. We have an established preceptorship programme in place and you will be well supported by your manager and colleagues and valued in your role. We offer opportunities for personal and professional development and you will receive regular clinical and safeguarding supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your skills and experience match the person specification we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details/informal visits contact: Margaret Bratherton North Team on: 07557545753&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are an equal opportunities employer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible Working opportunities are available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that non-NHS applicants with no previous NHS experience will ordinarily be appointed to the minimum of the salary band&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When providing references, these should be your two most recent employers (these may include your line manager or someone in a position of responsibility). Personal references are not acceptable.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
